==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ens
<hw>Ens</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧nz)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
<ets>ens</ets>, <ets>entis</ets>, a thing. See <er>Entity</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>Entity, being, or existence; an
actually existing being; also, God, as the Being of Beings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Something supposed to condense
within itself all the virtues and qualities of a substance from which it
is extracted; essence.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ensafe</ent>⟦br⟧
